# socioeconomic_ES

This is a Python library to ingest the most updated Spanish socioeconomic data regarding ....bla bla bla. 

## How to install the library?
1- Download the repository in your own system: git clone
2- Create library: python setup.py sdist
2- Install library: pip install dist/socioeconomic_ES-0.0.1.tar.gz

## How to use it?
```python
import socioeconomic_ES as sc

# Return the available collections
sc.get_collections() 

# Download all the socioeconomic data from all collections
sc.download()

# Download socioeconomic data in the `path` from the specified `collections`, `start year`, `end year`, and `municipality codes`. Decide whether to force gathering (True =  Do not take into account that datasets have already been downloaded).
sc.download(path,['INEcensus2021'], 2021, 2023, ['08001','08002'], False) 
```

